description: Since its Olympic debut in 1996, St. Lucia has never won a medal of any kind. Sha'Carri Richardson, who had entered the Paris Games as the 100-meter favorite, finished in second to win silver.
title: Julien Alfred stuns Sha'Carri Richardson in 100m to win St. Lucia's 1st Olympic gold

description: The attack took place Friday night near a hotel in a popular beachfront destination in Mogadishu. Nearly all of the people killed and injured were civilians, police said.
title: Islamic extremist group kills 32 people in attack on beachfront in Somalia's capital

description: The Yurchenko double pike, the most difficult vault in women's gymnastics, was named after Biles when she first landed it in international competition in 2023. Now, it has won her an Olympic gold.
title: Simone Biles wins her 3rd gold of the 2024 Olympics with the vault named after her

description: NPR's Scott Simon remembers Ina Jaffe, who first edited this program and later reported on seniors for NPR. Jaffe died this week at the age of 75.
title: Opinion: Remembering our colleague and friend, Ina Jaffe
